         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">30/8/83 ¶  ¶ It is very kind of you, dear Dr Bride, to think of Mr Fischer's offer. ¶ The publisher Theodor Fischer.See M to T. Bride, 29 March1883(in this edition as 83-03-29c);M to T. Bride,26 June ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.08.30</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Bride</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">83-133, unit 119, VPRS 805/P, inward registered correspondence, VA 913 Public Library of Victoria, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">30/8/83</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is very kind of you, dear Dr Bride, to think of Mr Fischer's offer.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The publisher Theodor Fischer.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>See M to T. Bride, 29 March<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1883<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 83-03-29c);<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to T. Bride,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>26 June 1883<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 83-06-26a);<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and T. Bride to M, 29 August 1883<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 83-08-29a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I hope, that the trustees at all events will secure some of the now available addenda to the Cassel-Issues, especially as Mr Fischer is likely to make a considerable reduction in the price as a favor to the Library.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Library decided on 24 September 1883 to order the works in question, and M was notified of this; see T. Bride to M, 26 September<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1883<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 83-09-26a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Herewith I beg to send you A D.C.'s "l'origine des plantes cultivées."<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Candolle (1883).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have a presentation-copy from the illustrious author, with whom I have been in correspondence for nearly 30 years; so I can spare the copy, ordered from my London-Bookseller.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
